  &lt;li&gt;Explaining complex issues in beautifully simple terms.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Listening way more than you talk and connecting with people.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Embracing change &amp;amp; adapting quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Managing multiple projects simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;A natural ability to see the full scope of a problem, in order to ask the right questions.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Never letting a detail fall through the cracks.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Using social media or web-based software, including Twitter, Facebook, Google Apps.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Familiarity with common help-desk/ticketing solutions such as Zendesk and Jira.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;How You Will Use Your Powers:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Saving clients across the country from any issues they are having.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Evaluate, troubleshoot, and follow-up on client issues as well as replicate and document for further escalation.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Develop support content including articles, blog posts, videos and other collateral. You may not author all that content, but you will work with our development and consulting teams to identify content needs and get them filled.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Being a voice for clients and fighting for their causes.&lt;/li&gt;
